reviews.text: If you've never been to this Green Bay iconic restaurant, you are missing out! Not only is the pizza fantastic, but they have gluten-free options that taste like real pizza! If you are gluten free, you know how important this is! We took our niece for her birthday and they made it so special, party song and special circus clown ice cream sundae! The games to play while you wait for pizza. Make it the perfect place for families! Caroline, our server made the night smooth, her service was excellent! Highly recommended!

You can tell this place has been around for a while and has a great reputation in the area. It was very loud in there as there is a small arcade. Very lively atmosphere and our server was very attentive and friendly. The pizza is decent, not really anything special but I think it's worth a visit to feel the spirit of green bay here
Our server Josie was awesome and helped us pick our pizza. Very friendly and knowledgeable about the food here. Thank you Happy Joe's and Josie for a wonderful experience after the Packer Game!

Completely inedible. Most disgusting pizza I‚Äôve ever had. That includes any frozen pizza, dominoes, Pizza Hut, etc. I would eat any other first. I‚Äôm so disgusted. And for the cost of it? Unbelievable. One of the most expensive pizzas we have tried and ordered while also being the nastiest.

We haven't been there in a long time but my daughter wanted to check it out. She has an egg allergy and sometimes it's hard going out. The server we had went above and beyond to make sure the ingredients did not have eggs in them. She was very knowledgeable about allergies and knew how to check for them and make sure that food items with eggs in them didn't touch her food. She was also very attentive and made our experience wonderful. We can't wait to go back!!

editorial_summary.overview: Kid-friendly pizza chain known for crust choices & Mexican-inspired pies plus oversized sundaes.

They don't deliver to the west side.  Think stadium hotels.   You'll have to pick up.
